# VPS Architecture -- {{ inventory_hostname }}

Managed by **catena** (Ansible). Do not edit system config files by hand
unless you know the Ansible role that manages them -- your changes will be
overwritten on the next converge.

## How things connect

```
Internet -> Cloudflare edge (TLS terminates here)
         -> Cloudflare Tunnel -> cloudflared container (dokploy-network)
         -> dokploy-traefik:80 (container, no host port binding)
         -> app containers (by Host header, via Traefik labels)
```

Operators and client staff reach the **Dokploy admin UI** at:
  `https://{{ dokploy_admin_hostname }}`
  Protected by self-hosted SSO (Keycloak + oauth2-proxy forward-auth).
  No Tailscale required.

Operators with Tailscale can **SSH** directly:
  `ssh ops@{{ ansible_host }}`

## Ports exposed on the host

**Traefik**: does NOT bind :80/:443 on the host. All app traffic enters via
the Cloudflare Tunnel, which connects to Traefik over Docker's
`dokploy-network`.

**Dokploy UI**: port 3000 is published in Swarm host mode (bound on all
interfaces), but **UFW restricts it to tailscale0 only**. Operators can
always reach `http://<tailnet-ip>:3000` over the tailnet, even if
cloudflared or CF Access is broken. Public access to :3000 is blocked by
UFW's default-deny + the tailscale0-only allow rule.

**SSH**: port 22, tailscale0 only (ufw_lockdown).

## Key paths

| Path | What | Managed by |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `/etc/dokploy/` | Dokploy config + Traefik | Dokploy install + roles/dokploy |
| `/etc/dokploy/traefik/dynamic/` | Traefik dynamic routes (admin, etc.) | roles/dokploy |
| `/etc/catena/` | Backup env, restic password | roles/backup |
| `{{ storage_mount_point }}/` | App data, Docker volumes, backups | roles/storage |
| `{{ storage_mount_point }}/docker/volumes/` | Named Docker volumes (app persistent data) | Docker / Dokploy |
| `{{ storage_mount_point }}/backup-staging/pg/` | pg_dumpall outputs | roles/backup wrapper |

## Backups

Nightly at {{ backup_schedule | default('03:30') }} via restic -> S3 (client-owned bucket).
Includes: named Docker volumes, app data, Dokploy config, SSH keys, fstab.
Excludes: Docker image layers (reproducible from registry).

**DO NOT configure Dokploy's built-in backup feature** -- verify restores with
the catena backup-verification flow instead. One backup tool, one restore path.

## Upgrades

**Dokploy**: `docker service update --image dokploy/dokploy:<new-version> dokploy`
followed by a catena site converge to re-apply hardening.

**System packages**: `unattended-upgrades` handles security patches automatically.
Full upgrades are operator-initiated.

## Do NOT

- Enable Let's Encrypt / HTTPS on Traefik. Cloudflare terminates TLS.
- Expose ports publicly via Docker `-p` flags. All public ingress is via the tunnel.
- Configure Dokploy's built-in backup (conflicts with restic strategy).
- Edit `/etc/ssh/sshd_config.d/10-catena.conf` by hand.
